 <entry>
  <title type="text">Announcing the release of wx_biz_data_crypt</title>
  <link rel="alternate" href="https://yanyingwang.github.io/2021/03/announcing-the-release-of-wx-biz-data-crypt.html?utm_source=english&amp;utm_medium=Atom" />
  <id>urn:https-yanyingwang-github-io:-2021-03-announcing-the-release-of-wx-biz-data-crypt-html</id>
  <published>2021-03-30T17:54:37Z</published>
  <updated>2021-03-30T17:54:37Z</updated>
  <author>
   <name>Yanying Wang</name></author>
  <content type="html">
&lt;p&gt;Recently I have been in the project to develop Wechat Mini programs, and when it comes to the part of decrypting data, I find out there does not exist a Ruby Gem for this although the Wechat official provides &lt;a href="https://res.wx.qq.com/wxdoc/dist/assets/media/aes-sample.eae1f364.zip"&gt;code sample&lt;/a&gt; but it is only for Python/PHP/C++. So I decided to resemble the Python source code and write a Ruby Gem based on it.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;a href="https://yanyingwang.github.io/2021/03/announcing-the-release-of-wx-biz-data-crypt.html?utm_source=english&amp;amp;utm_medium=Atom"&gt;&lt;em&gt;More&amp;hellip;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/a&gt;</content></entry>
 <entry>
  <title type="text">Fathoming out Racket Package's version</title>
  <link rel="alternate" href="https://yanyingwang.github.io/2021/03/fathoming-out-racket-package-s-version.html?utm_source=english&amp;utm_medium=Atom" />
  <id>urn:https-yanyingwang-github-io:-2021-03-fathoming-out-racket-package-s-version-html</id>
  <published>2021-03-29T01:30:34Z</published>
  <updated>2021-03-29T01:30:34Z</updated>
  <author>
   <name>Yanying Wang</name></author>
  <content type="html">
&lt;p&gt;Recently I received an email of &lt;a href="https://github.com/yanyingwang/http-client/commit/d7450cd2842f3d6da07e8167d4b1e0f1fa2572a6#r48314895"&gt;a github comment&lt;/a&gt; on a Racket Package of mine named &lt;a href="https://github.com/yanyingwang/http-client/"&gt;http-client&lt;/a&gt;, which was announced to release by my post of &lt;a href="2020/09/announcing-the-release-of-http-client.html"&gt;Announcing the release of http-client&lt;/a&gt;. Until then, I realized there really exist someone using my packages except me. This also make me realize I already came to the point to fathom out the design of Racket&amp;rsquo;s package version that I tried before and abandoned because of being short on time, and I should commit to add versions to my packages.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;a href="https://yanyingwang.github.io/2021/03/fathoming-out-racket-package-s-version.html?utm_source=english&amp;amp;utm_medium=Atom"&gt;&lt;em&gt;More&amp;hellip;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/a&gt;</content></entry>
